acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

params._argsEqualityCheckEnforcer: The address of the ArgsEqualityCheckEnforcer contract.
params._delegationManager: The address of the trusted DelegationManager contract has privileged access to call        executeByExecutor based on a given delegation.
params._metaSwap: The address of the trusted MetaSwap contract.
params._owner: The initial owner of the contract.

executeFromExecutor(bytes32,bytes).details: Only callable by the DelegationManager. Supports single-call execution,         and handles the revert logic via ExecType.Related: @erc7579/MSAAdvanced.sol

params._executionCalldata: The encoded call data (single) to be executed.
params._mode: The encoded execution mode of the transaction (CallType, ExecType, etc.).

returns.returnData_: An array of returned data from each executed call.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

swapByDelegation((bytes,uint256,bytes),(.details: The msg.sender must be the leaf delegator

params._delegations: Array of Delegation objects containing delegation-specific data, sorted leaf to root.
params._signatureData: Includes: - apiData Encoded swap parameters, used by the aggregator. - expiration Timestamp after which the signature is invalid. - signature Signature validating the provided apiData.
params._useTokenWhitelist: Indicates whether the tokens must be validated or not.

swapTokens(string,address,address,addres.details: This function can only be called internally by this contract (`onlySelf`).

params._aggregatorId: The identifier for the swap aggregator/DEX aggregator.
params._amountFrom: The amount of tokens to be swapped.
params._balanceFromBefore: The contract's balance of _tokenFrom before the incoming token transfer is credited.
params._recipient: The address that will receive the swapped tokens.
params._swapData: Arbitrary data required by the aggregator (e.g. encoded swap params).
params._tokenFrom: The input token of the swap.
params._tokenTo: The output token of the swap.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

updateAllowedAggregatorIds(string[],bool.details: Only callable by the contract owner.

params._statuses: Corresponding array of booleans (true = allowed, false = disallowed).

updateAllowedTokens(address[],bool[]).details: Only callable by the contract owner.

params._statuses: Corresponding array of booleans to set each token's allowed status.

withdraw(address,uint256,address).details: Only callable by the contract owner.

params._amount: The amount of tokens (or native) to withdraw.
params._recipient: The address to receive the withdrawn tokens.
params._token: The token to be withdrawn (use address(0) for native token).

executeFromExecutor(bytes32,bytes).notice: Executes one calls on behalf of this contract,         authorized by the DelegationManager.

setSwapApiSigner(address).notice: Updates the address authorized to sign API requests.

swapByDelegation((bytes,uint256,bytes),(.notice: Executes a token swap using a delegation and transfers the swapped tokens to the root delegator, after validating signature and expiration.

swapTokens(string,address,address,addres.notice: Executes the actual token swap via the MetaSwap contract and transfer the output tokens to the recipient.

updateAllowedAggregatorIds(string[],bool.notice: Updates the allowed (whitelist) status of multiple aggregator IDs in a single call.

updateAllowedTokens(address[],bool[]).notice: Updates the allowed (whitelist) status of multiple tokens in a single call.

withdraw(address,uint256,address).notice: Withdraws a specified token from the contract to a recipient.
